{"title":"Canyon Release Spectral Mullet K.I.S. with Steering Stabilizer","link":"https://bikerumor.com/canyon-spectral-mullet-k-i-s-steering-stabilizer/","date":1689670800000,"content":"<p>The Canyon Spectral Mullet, a 150mm travel mountain bike that is exclusively coil-sprung, is now available in a K.IS. model featuring steering-stabilization technology developed by Syntace. The “Keep It Stable” contraption is a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/syntace-kis-bike-steering-stabilizer-aims-to-keep-it-straight-stable-simple/\" target=\"_blank\">self-centering device for your steerer tube</a>, utilizing two coil springs, straps (ultra-strong polymer fiber bands) and a cam that couples the device securely to your steerer via clamping. It lives inside the bike’s top tube, with only the mounting points and spring pre-load adjustment visible from the outside.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"canyon spectral mullet kis steering stabilizer\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-steering-stabilizer-steerer-tube-self-centering-device-syntace.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>For now, only the Canyon Spectral bikes benefit from K.I.S., though we did see <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-lenzerheide-world-cup-dh-new-bikes-tech/\" target=\"_blank\">Troy Brosnan’s Sender rocking one at Lenzerheide World Cup</a> earlier this year.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Our EU Tech Editor, Cory Benson, has some <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/first-ride-canyon-spectral-kis-adds-light-steering-stabilizer-to-climb-descend-faster/\" target=\"_blank\">thoughts on how the K.I.S. changes the ride feel</a>, based on his experience aboard the Canyon Spectral 29. At launch, only that dedicated 29″ platform benefited from the steering-stabilizer, and it was offered only to customers in Europe. Now, the Canyon Spectral Mullet K.I.S. gets it, too… and it’s yours for $4,699 USD. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"canyon spectral mullet kis us build kit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-kis-mullet-150mm-mtb-us-build-kit.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Canyon Spectral Mullet K.I.S.</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Canyon Spectral Mullet K.I.S. is $500 more expensive than the CF 8 CLLCTV model (<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-canyon-spectral-mullet-cf-cllctv-shifts-capable-trail-bike-to-enduro/\" target=\"_blank\">reviewed here</a>) which is <em>sans K.I.S.</em> That said, the two build kits differ considerably in departments of suspension, wheels and drivetrain. Without further ado, here’s what you get for your $4,699 USD // 4,999 €…</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Carbon Frame (ASTM Category 4) with 150mm Rear Wheel Travel</li>\n\n\n\n<li>160mm RockShox Lyrik Select+ Fork</li>\n\n\n\n<li>RockShox Super Deluxe Coil Select+ Shock</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM GX Eagle AXS with 10-52T Cassette (Replaced by <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-gx-eagle-transmission-t-type-review/\" target=\"_blank\">GX Transmission</a> for Customers in Europe)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>DT Swiss EX511 Rims with 370 LN Ratchet Hubset</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Maxxis Assegai Front and DHRII (EXO+ MaxxTerra) Rear Tires</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM 4-piston Code R 4-Piston Brakes and Centerline Rotors</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"rockshox lyrik select+ 160mm canyon spectral mullet kis\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-rockshox-lyrik-select-fork.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-cf8-rockshox-super-deluxe-select-coil-shock.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-cf8-rockshox-super-deluxe-select-coil-shock-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"canyon spectral mullet kis super deluxe coil shock\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-cf8-rockshox-super-deluxe-select-coil-shock-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-cf8-rockshox-super-deluxe-select-coil-shock-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/canyon-spectral-mullet-kis-cf8-rockshox-super-deluxe-select-coil-shock-120x68.jpg 120w, 